The paper deals with graph decomposition, which is a topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves distance-related graph problems, which are often studied in the context of graph theory and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of low diameter decompositions involves geometric concepts such as ball growing, which is a technique used in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses algorithms for large-scale computation, which can be categorized under numerical analysis (cs.NA) or scientific computing (cs.SI).
